    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 13B-REW twin-rotor engine with its complex sequential turbocharging system intact. This unit maintains strong compression and transitions smoothly between primary and secondary boost phases. The chassis retains its legendary 50/50 weight distribution, supported by factory forged aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Recent preventative maintenance includes a cooling system overhaul and inspection of the vacuum line 'rat's nest' to ensure pneumatic integrity. While the exterior shows honest patina consistent with a well-enjoyed enthusiast vehicle, the mechanical vitals remain robust, offering a pure, analog driving experience.",
